"{\"uid\": \"metro.co.uk-2024-08-06-women-wear-headguards-not-men-olympic-boxing-21369308\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"Boxing fans will have been tuning in to catch the action at theParis2024Olympicsover the past week.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 99, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Boxing fans\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 11}, {\"ngram\": \"the action\", \"from\": 46, \"to\": 56}, {\"ngram\": \"theParis2024Olympicsover\", \"from\": 60, \"to\": 84}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And you do not need to be eagle-eyed to have noticed that male boxers have not been wearing headguards during their rounds, while the women boxers have been donning red and blue headgear.\", \"from\": 101, \"to\": 288, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"male boxers\", \"from\": 159, \"to\": 170}, {\"ngram\": \"headguards\", \"from\": 193, \"to\": 203}, {\"ngram\": \"their rounds\", \"from\": 211, \"to\": 223}, {\"ngram\": \"the women boxers\", \"from\": 231, \"to\": 247}, {\"ngram\": \"red and blue headgear\", \"from\": 266, \"to\": 287}]}, {\"sentence\": \"You'd also be forgiven for being curious about the difference, and if there is a particular health and safety reason for it.\", \"from\": 290, \"to\": 414, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the difference\", \"from\": 337, \"to\": 351}, {\"ngram\": \"a particular health and safety reason\", \"from\": 369, \"to\": 406}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Follow Metro.co.uk's live blog for updates from the Paris 2024 Olympics Here's what we know.\", \"from\": 416, \"to\": 509, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Follow Metro.co.uk's live blog\", \"from\": 416, \"to\": 446}, {\"ngram\": \"updates\", \"from\": 451, \"to\": 458}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paris 2024 Olympics\", \"from\": 464, \"to\": 487}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Female boxers wear headguards at the Olympics because of rules set by the Olympic Committee (IOC) and the International Boxing Association (IBA).\", \"from\": 511, \"to\": 656, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 617, \"end\": 649, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women's_International_Boxing_Association\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.1449297171732148e-24, \"text\": \"International Boxing Association\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women's_International_Boxing_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women's_International_Boxing_Association\"}, {\"begin\": 651, \"end\": 654, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"score\": 0.9887812777859024, \"rank\": 0.011331998472522184, \"text\": \"IBA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Female boxers\", \"from\": 511, \"to\": 524}, {\"ngram\": \"headguards\", \"from\": 530, \"to\": 540}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 544, \"to\": 556}, {\"ngram\": \"rules\", \"from\": 568, \"to\": 573}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic Committee\", \"from\": 581, \"to\": 602}, {\"ngram\": \"IOC\", \"from\": 604, \"to\": 607}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Before the 2016 Olympics in Rio, both male and female athletes were made to wear headguards to improve their safety and to reduce concussions.\", \"from\": 658, \"to\": 800, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 686, \"end\": 689, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999931423304623, \"rank\": 6.857716636099413e-06, \"text\": \"Rio\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the 2016 Olympics\", \"from\": 665, \"to\": 682}, {\"ngram\": \"both male and female athletes\", \"from\": 691, \"to\": 720}, {\"ngram\": \"headguards\", \"from\": 739, \"to\": 749}, {\"ngram\": \"their safety\", \"from\": 761, \"to\": 773}, {\"ngram\": \"concussions\", \"from\": 788, \"to\": 799}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The decision was made after South Korean Fighter Kim Duk-Koo died after a world championship bout in 1982.\", \"from\": 802, \"to\": 908, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 836, \"end\": 842, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Korean_language\", \"score\": 0.9973515665957767, \"rank\": 0.002619006448460243, \"text\": \"Korean\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Korean_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Korean_language\"}, {\"begin\": 851, \"end\": 862, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kim_Duk-koo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kim Duk-Koo\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kim_Duk-koo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kim_Duk-koo\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The decision\", \"from\": 802, \"to\": 814}, {\"ngram\": \"a world championship bout\", \"from\": 874, \"to\": 899}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The IOC and IOA subsequently mandated that fighters at the Olympics, who are amateurs, must wear head protection for their own safety.\", \"from\": 910, \"to\": 1044, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 914, \"end\": 917, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.9378436481752114e-20, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 922, \"end\": 925, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indian_Olympic_Association\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"IOA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indian_Olympic_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indian_Olympic_Association\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"fighters\", \"from\": 953, \"to\": 961}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 965, \"to\": 977}, {\"ngram\": \"amateurs\", \"from\": 987, \"to\": 995}, {\"ngram\": \"head protection\", \"from\": 1007, \"to\": 1022}, {\"ngram\": \"their own safety\", \"from\": 1027, \"to\": 1043}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, this changed in 2016 when a study from the Global Sport Institute revealed that boxers fighting with no head gear were less likely to suffer concussions.\", \"from\": 1046, \"to\": 1208, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a study\", \"from\": 1081, \"to\": 1088}, {\"ngram\": \"the Global Sport Institute\", \"from\": 1094, \"to\": 1120}, {\"ngram\": \"boxers\", \"from\": 1135, \"to\": 1141}, {\"ngram\": \"no head gear\", \"from\": 1156, \"to\": 1168}, {\"ngram\": \"concussions\", \"from\": 1196, \"to\": 1207}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This allowed men to fight without headgear, but given the study was only conducted on males, the IOC decided that women should continue to wear headgear out of an abundance of caution.\", \"from\": 1210, \"to\": 1394, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1307, \"end\": 1310, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.9378436481752114e-20, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"men\", \"from\": 1223, \"to\": 1226}, {\"ngram\": \"headgear\", \"from\": 1244, \"to\": 1252}, {\"ngram\": \"the study\", \"from\": 1264, \"to\": 1273}, {\"ngram\": \"males\", \"from\": 1296, \"to\": 1301}, {\"ngram\": \"women\", \"from\": 1324, \"to\": 1329}, {\"ngram\": \"headgear\", \"from\": 1354, \"to\": 1362}, {\"ngram\": \"an abundance\", \"from\": 1370, \"to\": 1382}, {\"ngram\": \"caution\", \"from\": 1386, \"to\": 1393}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In 2013, theWall Street Journalwrote that then-chairman of the AIBA medical commission, Dr Charles Butler, explained that concussion was less of an issue with women fighters due to their strength.\", \"from\": 1396, \"to\": 1592, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1487, \"end\": 1501, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catherine_Butler\", \"score\": 0.9281736684260192, \"rank\": 0.04674126860187735, \"text\": \"Charles Butler\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catherine_Butler\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catherine_Butler\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"In 2013, theWall Street Journalwrote\", \"from\": 1396, \"to\": 1432}, {\"ngram\": \"then-chairman\", \"from\": 1438, \"to\": 1451}, {\"ngram\": \"the AIBA medical commission\", \"from\": 1455, \"to\": 1482}, {\"ngram\": \"concussion\", \"from\": 1518, \"to\": 1528}, {\"ngram\": \"an issue\", \"from\": 1541, \"to\": 1549}, {\"ngram\": \"women fighters\", \"from\": 1555, \"to\": 1569}, {\"ngram\": \"their strength\", \"from\": 1577, \"to\": 1591}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, in 2021,Naturereported that women sports players are at greater risk of traumatic brain injuries, and often 'fare worse' after a concussion, than their male counterparts.\", \"from\": 1594, \"to\": 1773, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"women sports players\", \"from\": 1631, \"to\": 1651}, {\"ngram\": \"greater risk\", \"from\": 1659, \"to\": 1671}, {\"ngram\": \"traumatic brain injuries\", \"from\": 1675, \"to\": 1699}, {\"ngram\": \"a concussion\", \"from\": 1730, \"to\": 1742}, {\"ngram\": \"their male counterparts\", \"from\": 1749, \"to\": 1772}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Following the rule change, an observationalstudy published in 2017concurred that 'the number of stoppages due to head blows was significantly decreased without headguards' in male boxing.\", \"from\": 1775, \"to\": 1962, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the rule change\", \"from\": 1785, \"to\": 1800}, {\"ngram\": \"an observationalstudy\", \"from\": 1802, \"to\": 1823}, {\"ngram\": \"the number\", \"from\": 1857, \"to\": 1867}, {\"ngram\": \"stoppages\", \"from\": 1871, \"to\": 1880}, {\"ngram\": \"head blows\", \"from\": 1888, \"to\": 1898}, {\"ngram\": \"headguards\", \"from\": 1935, \"to\": 1945}, {\"ngram\": \"male boxing\", \"from\": 1950, \"to\": 1961}]}, {\"sentence\": \"All minors (boys and girls), schoolchildren, juniors, youth and Senior Elite and Senior Development Females must also fight with headwear.\", \"from\": 1964, \"to\": 2102, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"All minors\", \"from\": 1964, \"to\": 1974}, {\"ngram\": \"boys\", \"from\": 1976, \"to\": 1980}, {\"ngram\": \"girls\", \"from\": 1985, \"to\": 1990}, {\"ngram\": \"schoolchildren\", \"from\": 1993, \"to\": 2007}, {\"ngram\": \"juniors\", \"from\": 2009, \"to\": 2016}, {\"ngram\": \"youth\", \"from\": 2018, \"to\": 2023}, {\"ngram\": \"Senior Elite and Senior Development Females\", \"from\": 2028, \"to\": 2071}, {\"ngram\": \"headwear\", \"from\": 2093, \"to\": 2101}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Follow Metro across our social channels, onFacebook,TwitterandInstagram Share your views in the comments below ArrowMORE:Adam Peaty reveals grim Olympic Village catering; says 'worms' are found in food ArrowMORE:Swimmer kicked out of Olympic Village hits back at claims of 'inappropriate' behaviour ArrowMORE:Paula Radcliffe speaks out on Olympic disqualification controversy - before stunning U-turn Punchy analysis, transfer talk and more from Metro's football experts, sent straight to your inbox every week.\", \"from\": 2104, \"to\": 2620, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2227, \"end\": 2237, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adam_Peaty\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Adam Peaty\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adam_Peaty\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adam_Peaty\"}, {\"begin\": 2251, \"end\": 2266, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\", \"score\": 0